@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy | ToolNexus";
    ViewData["Description"] = "Review the ToolNexus privacy policy, including data handling, storage practices, and your responsibilities when using tools.";
    ViewData["CanonicalUrl"] = $"{Context.Request.Scheme}://{Context.Request.Host}/privacy";
    ViewData["Keywords"] = "ToolNexus privacy policy, developer tools data policy";
}

<article class="static-page legal-page page-shell" aria-label="ToolNexus privacy policy">
    <header class="static-page__header">
        <h1>Privacy</h1>
        <p>ToolNexus is designed for fast utility workflows with clear privacy expectations.</p>
    </header>

    <nav class="static-page__section static-page__nav" aria-label="Privacy quick links">
        <h2>Privacy resources</h2>
        <ul class="static-page__link-list">
            <li><a href="/disclaimer">Read legal disclaimer</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contact-us">Contact us about privacy questions</a></li>
            <li><a href="/tools">Browse tools before sharing data</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Data you provide</h2>
        <p>Input data you submit is used to execute requested tool actions and return outputs. Avoid submitting confidential, regulated, or sensitive personal information unless you fully understand associated risks.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Operational telemetry</h2>
        <p>We may collect operational metrics such as request volume, latency, and anonymized usage events to maintain reliability, improve performance, and detect abuse.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Storage and retention</h2>
        <p>Temporary processing artifacts may be retained for caching, diagnostics, and service protection. Retention windows are limited to operational needs and system security requirements.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Third-party services</h2>
        <p>ToolNexus may use trusted infrastructure providers for hosting and delivery. These providers process infrastructure metadata under their own security and compliance controls.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Privacy FAQ</h2>
        <div class="static-page__faq-list" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage">
            <article class="static-page__faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                <h3 itemprop="name">Does ToolNexus store my tool input forever?</h3>
                <p itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"><span itemprop="text">No. Processing artifacts are retained only for short-lived operational and security requirements.</span></p>
            </article>
            <article class="static-page__faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                <h3 itemprop="name">Should I submit confidential records?</h3>
                <p itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"><span itemprop="text">Avoid submitting confidential or regulated data unless your security and compliance teams have approved this workflow.</span></p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Practical privacy checklist for engineers</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Mask secrets, tokens, and customer identifiers before pasting data.</li>
            <li>Use synthetic payloads for demos and troubleshooting whenever possible.</li>
            <li>Review organizational policy before processing regulated records.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For low-risk testing, start in <a href="/tools/json-formatter">JSON Formatter</a> or <a href="/tools/yaml-to-json">YAML to JSON</a> with sample data.</p>
    </section>
</article>
